title: Grateful Dead Live at Capital Centre on 1993-03-18
lineage: Soundfield ST250's (FOB) > DAT > Panasonic SV-3800 > HHb CDR-850 > CDR > EAC 0.9 beta 4 (secure) > Soundforge 5 > CD Wave > shntool > SHN
description: Hell In A Bucket-> Sugaree, Walkin' Blues, Broken Arrow, Loose Lucy, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Friend Of The Devil, The Music Never Stopped China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Way To Go Home, Wave To The Wind-> Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> Corinna-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: I Fought The Law

reviews.review_text: An Overlooked Gem Check out the second set of this show, if you enjoy the Bruce factor. I found his accordion a nice addition to China Cat and Estimated. Of course, as always, Hornsby adds a strong shot of energy to the band. A very nice China>Rider... Superb Estimated and segue jam into an unexpected Terrapin...Corrina out of drums was very nice...Heck, even Wave to the Wind was well played. Wave had some good potential jamming , if you could get over the awkward vocals. Overall an excellent show, worth a D/L

One COLD show We drove from philly to see the show, we parked next to a couple with PA plates, smoking a bowl in the car, several years later I would run into the same people at a Reggae Fest in Philly, Funny how I remembered them.  IT WAS COLD COLD outside, shiveriing in the parking lot before the show.  BUT, INSIDE this place was GETTING HOT.  I GOOD MEMORY in a world of melted memories.

My first This was my first show ever...I had no idea what a treat I was getting, but I enjoyed the hell out of it. 

Listened to it again finally about 5 years ago and realized how lucky I was. I'm kinda biased, but I'd say download this one to hear one of the latter day semi-precious gems.

GD 3/18/93 Great aud tape
 -- fun show, Corrina kills me in person, always has
...broken arrow was raw but Phil on the mike always made it a great night...

mellow but tasty -- 
3+

I was standing outside (wondering where my ticket was) Arrrgh! Listening to this show is sort of bitter sweet. A friend's father was supposed to have "hooked us up" with some tickets, but they were not waiting at the Will Call office- man that sucked. It was one of those dazed confused feelings (in a really bad way). Kind of like finding out Santa Claus died on his way down your chimney and the presents also burned up. LOL. 

But I made it to the summer shows in D.C. so it was all good. But damn, I wish I could have heard this live...
cap center the 3 shows were just awesome.

good show, but recording is "chatty" this is a pretty well played show by the GD...the recording suffers from loud crowd noise and some taper issues...this mic set up is very good and expensive but like real estate location is everything...try looking for the schoeps source...FOB's are only good when the crowd is cool
